rumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044930/2021-transition-patrol-mullet-enduro-mountain-bike-alloy-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044930/2021-transition-patrol-mullet-enduro-mountain-bike-alloy-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044930/2021-transition-patrol-mullet-enduro-mountain-bike-alloy-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044930/2021-transition-patrol-mullet-enduro-mountain-bike-alloy-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>A refresh for the Transition Patrol is overdue, with the last meaningful geometry update seen in 2018. Of course we were expecting to see longer reach figures, a slacker head tube angle and a steeper seat tube angle, but we weren’t necessarily expecting a mixed wheel size bike.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>So, what are the geometry figures for the 2021 Transition Patrol, and are they adjustable?</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust.jpg\" alt=\"2021 transition patrol flip chip geometry adjustment\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-696x1044.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-1068x1602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-280x420.jpg 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-696x1044.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-1068x1602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044821/mullet-transition-patrol-flip-chip-geometry-adjust-280x420.jpg 280w\"></a></p><p>We have two geometry charts for you to froth over, with a flip-chip at the bottom shock mount offering two configurations. In the high setting, a 63.5° head angle (actually a lot slacker than most brand’s low setting) and a 78.1° effective seat tube angle sit between a 480mm reach. We’re really pleased to see these much steeper seat tube angles becoming more mainstream as it can make these long travel bikes much easier to pedal to the top.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting.jpg\" alt=\"mullet transition patrol high geometry setting\" width=\"1200\" height=\"956\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-297x237.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-800x637.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-768x612.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-696x554.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-1068x851.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-527x420.jpg 527w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-297x237.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-800x637.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-768x612.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-696x554.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-1068x851.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044641/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-high-setting-527x420.jpg 527w\"></a></p><p>In the low setting, the HA drops to 63° as the bottom bracket drops 5mm to 333mm. This concomitantly slackens the seat tube angle to a (still healthy) effective 77.6° and reduces reach by 5mm. For those who want to slacken the head angle beyond 63° without making the seat angle slacker, the 56mm/56mm headset will happily take an angle set.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting.jpg\" alt=\"mullet transition patrol low geometry setting\" width=\"1200\" height=\"956\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-297x237.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-800x637.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-768x612.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-696x554.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-1068x851.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-527x420.jpg 527w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-297x237.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-800x637.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-768x612.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-696x554.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-1068x851.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044406/mullet-transition-patrol-geometry-low-setting-527x420.jpg 527w\"></a></p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>That headset will also take a reach adjusting headset, permitting the use of a dual-crown fork. Swapping out the stock 205mm x 60mm shock for a 65mm stroke increases the rear wheel travel to 170mm, giving riders the option to turn a nippy enduro bike into something rather more ambitious.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"2021 transition patrol alloy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045726/transition-patrol-alloy-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><h3>GiddyUp Suspension Kinematic</h3><p>The Transition Patrol is available in S, M, L and XL. The smaller bikes get 436mm chainstays while the stays on the L and XL bikes are longer at 440mm. That results in two slightly different leverage curves, with the longer stays displaying the more linear curve.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves.jpg\" alt=\"2021 transition patrol leverage curves\" width=\"1200\" height=\"723\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-297x179.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-800x482.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-768x463.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-696x419.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-1068x643.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-697x420.jpg 697w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-297x179.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-800x482.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-768x463.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-696x419.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-1068x643.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28044412/mullet-transition-patrol-leverage-curves-697x420.jpg 697w\"></a></p><p>The latest iteration of Transition’s GiddyUp suspension kinematic gives the Patrol 24% overall progression. The marketers tell us this gives it “an excellent balance of support and small bump sensitivity. Anti-squat is tuned to enhance pedaling performance and provides a platform to push against when pumping, without sacrificing a bottomless feel when needed”.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260277\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260277\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol.jpg\" alt=\"hannah bergman sends massive jump in woods 2021 transition patrol\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28045944/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260277\">Hannah Bergman demonstrates the full capability of the 2021 Transition Patrol</figcaption></figure><p>Speaking of a bottomless feel; there is clearance for, and sufficient bottom-out resistance in the leverage curve to allow riders to swap out the stock air shock for a coil option. Transition suggest a sag range of 27 – 33%, allowing riders some freedom to tune the feel of the bike according to their riding style and local trails.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span></p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-HWSunYIReU?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><h3>Frame Details</h3><p>The 2021 Transition Patrol runs a 6061 aluminium frame with Boost (12mm x 148mm) rear axle spacing. The stays permit clearance for tires up to 2.6″ wide. We’re waiting to hear back from Transition on what the maximum rear brake rotor diameter is.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details.jpg\" alt=\"2021 transition patrol\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052015/2021-transition-patrol-frame-details-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The frame runs a threaded bottom bracket and a 55mm/56mm press-in headset. Cables are routed internally for the rear derailleur and dropper seat post while routing for the rear brake is external. There is room within the front triangle for a water bottle and there is an accessory mount on the underside of the top tube to aid packless setups.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering.jpg\" alt=\"hannah bergman riding 2021 transition patrol\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052945/hannah-bergmann-2021-transition-patrol-cornering-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The pivots get Enduro Max Sealed Bearings while the main pivot also gets extra protection against water ingress and trail crud in the form of bearing shields. The chainstay, seatstay (drive side only) and downtubes each get a rubber molded protection against chain slap and rock strikes. Finally, the bike runs a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/09/10/sram-introduces-universal-derailleur-hanger-concept-and-its-brilliant/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SRAM UDH</a> derailleur hanger, making a replacement easy to source.</p><h3>Final Fun Fact</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052632/transition-dirtbag-mullet-lars-sternerg.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052632/transition-dirtbag-mullet-lars-sternerg.jpg\" alt=\