768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052938/hannah-bergman-2021-transition-patrol-mullet-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052938/hannah-bergman-2021-transition-patrol-mullet-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28052938/hannah-bergman-2021-transition-patrol-mullet-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The 2021 Patrol is only available in alloy at the moment. Historically, Transition have offered a carbon model so expect one to drop in due course.</p><p>While we know bikes will be available this summer, we don’t yet have any info on models and pricing. We can tell you that every model will feature a OneUp Components V2 Dropper Post and Bash Guard, with 165mm crank arms stock. Stay tuned.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors.jpg\" alt=\"2021 transition patrol raw blueberry blue colors\" width=\"1200\" height=\"555\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors-297x137.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors-800x370.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/28054858/2021-transition-patrol-colors-120x56.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2